cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for de-identification of clinical notes. The use of deep learning techniques and word embeddings further supports this categorization. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper presents a deep learning architecture for the task. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the use of advanced NLP techniques for a specific application in the healthcare domain. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible sub-category as de-identification is a crucial step in protecting patient privacy and ensuring data security. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the task of removing protected health information from clinical notes, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
